This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with language identification in speech processing applications. It may also belong to cs.SD (Sound) and cs.SI (Signal Processing) as it involves processing of audio signals. Additionally, it may be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it employs an end-to-end network for language identification. Finally, it may also be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the development of an automated system for language identification.
